.SS "ntp MODULE OPTIONS"

.P
The packet header structure is based on RFC 5905,
section "7.3. Packet Header Variables".

The \fItimestamp\fR argument used below is a 64-bit value in the range
of {0..0xffffffff\fB.\fR0xffffffff} and
represents seconds since 1900-01-01 00:00:00.0 (the integer part gets stored
in the first 32-bit, the fractional part as number of 1/0xffffffff units
in the second 32-bit). If the \fItimestamp\fR does not contain a dot (\fB.\fR),
the value gets parsed as a 64-bit \fIrnum\fR (if you use a hex number, remember
that on little endian machines the 1st 32-bit and 2nd 32-bit get swapped).
If the \fItimestamp\fR contains a dot and starts with a plus (\fB+\fR), the
time in seconds between 1900-01-01 00:00:00 and 1970-01-01 00:00:00 gets added
to the integer part for convenience, so that one may use the output of
UNIX timestamp utilities like GNU date or ksh directly,
e.g. "printf\ '+%(%s)T.0'\ '2018\-04\-16\ 17:16:02\ UTC'".

.TP
-nl\ \fInum\fR
Set the NTP \fBLeap Indicator\fR to \fInum\fR {0..3}. Default:\ 0 (no warning)
.TP
-nv\ \fInum\fR
Set the NTP \fBversion\fR of this packet to \fInum\fR {0..7}. Default:\ 4
.TP
-nm\ \fInum\fR
Set the NTP \fBmode\fR to \fInum\fR {0..7}. Default:\ 0
.TP
-ns\ \fInum\fR
Set the \fBstratum\fR to \fInum\fR {0..255}.
Default:\ 0 (unspecified)
.TP
-nP\ \fInum\fR
Set the \fBpoll\fR interval to \fInum\fR {-128..127} (log2 seconds).
Default:\ 6
.TP
-np\ \fInum\fR
Set the \fBprecision\fR of system clock field
to \fInum\fR {-128..127} (log2 seconds).
Default:\ 0
.TP
-ne\ \fIdouble\fR|\fInum\fR
Set the total round-trip delay to the reference clock (\fBroot delay\fB) to
the given value.
If the value contains a dot (\fB.\fR) than the value is expected to
represent a \fIdouble\fR.
Otherwise it gets parsed as a \fInum\fR {0..0xffffffff}.
Default:\ 0.0
.TP
-nd\ \fIdouble\fR|\fInum\fR
Set the estimated drift rate (\fBroot dispersion\fR) to the
given value.
If the value contains a dot (\fB.\fR) than the value is expected to
represent a \fIdouble\fR.
Otherwise it gets parsed as a \fInum\fR {0..0xffffffff}.
Default:\ 0.0
.TP
-nr\ \fIv4addr\fR|\fIID\fR
Set the NTP \fBreference clock\fR to the given IP \fIv4addr\fRess
or \fIID\fR (string with max. 4 characters not starting with a digit).
Default: 0
.TP
-nf\ \fItimestamp\fR
Set the \fBreference\fR \fItimestamp\fR.
Default: 0.0
.TP
-no\ \fItimestamp\fR
Set the \fBoriginate\fR \fItimestamp\fR. Default: 0.0
.TP
-na\ \fItimestamp\fR
Set the arrival (\fBreceive\fR) \fItimestamp\fR. Default: 0.0
.TP
-nx\ \fItimestamp\fR
Set the NTP xmit (\fBtransmit\fR) \fItimestamp\fR. Default: 0.0
